  {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## 2. Collections\nLists, tuples, sets, and dictionaries are fundamental Python collections."]},

  {"cell_type": "code", "metadata": {}, "source": ["numbers = [1,2,3,4,5]\nprint('List:', numbers)\n\npoint = (10,20)\nprint('Tuple:', point)\n\nfruits = {'apple','banana','cherry'}\nprint('Set:', fruits)\n\nstudent_scores = {'Alice':90,'Bob':85}\nprint('Dictionary:', student_scores)"]},

  {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## 3. Operators\nPython supports arithmetic, comparison, logical, bitwise, membership, identity, and unpacking operators."]},

  {"cell_type": "code", "metadata": {}, "source": ["a, b = 10, 3\nprint('Addition:', a + b)\nprint('Subtraction:', a - b)\nprint('Multiplication:', a * b)\nprint('Division:', a / b)\nprint('Floor division:', a // b)\nprint('Modulus:', a % b)\nprint('Exponent:', a ** b)"]},

  {"cell_type": "code", "metadata": {}, "source": ["x, y = 5, 10\nprint('Equal:', x == y)\nprint('Not equal:', x != y)\nprint('Less than:', x < y)\nprint('Greater or equal:', x >= y)\nprint('Logical AND:', x < y and y > 0)\nprint('Logical OR:', x > y or y > 0)\nprint('Logical NOT:', not(x < y))"]},

  {"cell_type": "code", "metadata": {}, "source": ["# Unpacking\nnumbers = [1,2,3,4]\na, *rest = numbers\nprint('First:', a, 'Rest:', rest)\ndata = {'x':1,'y':2}\nnew_data = {**data,'z':3}\nprint('Merged dict:', new_data)"]},

